fields.physical_description:
The car is very dark blue with silver grill, bumper and lights; rear lights are red.  On the bonnet of the car is a black and white paper label printed to show the globe and man trademark of the programme together with U.N.C.L.E.Mounted on the car bonnet are two silver spotlights which turn, and on the roof is a silver trigger mechanism which when depressed operate the driver and passenger.  These figures are holding guns and when the trigger is pressed, each moves out of the window while the trigger clicks.  The windows are tinted greenish yellow plastic and three `bullet' marks are shown on the front one.  The interior is yellow plastic with the driver having black hair to represent Napoleon Solo played by Robert Vaughan and blond Ilya Kuryakin, played by David McCallum.   The underside is grey and the wheels silver with black tyres.

Oldsmobile Super 88 was issued in December 1962 and deleted in 1966, price 4/9d.  It was the Canadian version in light blue and white, grey/blue, and dark blue.  A special livery, red and gold, was done in 1966 for the International London Toy Fair, with special box, 5/6d.
fields.title: the man from u.n.c.l.e. car, 497
